%C3%A9%2C%20a%20West%20African%20coffee%20shop%20in%20New%20Jersey.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIn%202023%2C%20when%20the%20building%20housing%20the%20caf%C3%A9%20went%20up%20for%20sale%2C%20he%20and%20his%20friend%20bought%20it%20together.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThey%20turned%20the%20building's%20apartments%20into%20Airbnbs%2C%20charging%20guests%20between%20%24140%20and%20%24175%20per%20day.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Isreal%20Adeyanju%2C%2032%2C%20a%20coffee%20shop%20owner%20and%20Airbnb%20host%20in%20Jersey%20City%2C%20New%20Jersey.%20In%202023%2C%20Adeyanju%20and%20his%20friend%20Samuel%20Osei-Afriyie%2C%20both%20partial%20owners%20of%20K%E1%BB%8D%20Caf%C3%A9%2C%20purchased%20the%20building%20where%20they%20had%20been%20leasing%20space%20for%20the%20coffee%20shop.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThey%20partnered%20with%20Nestment%2C%20a%20real%20estate%20company%2C%20to%20help%20facilitate%20the%20purchase.%20Adeyanju%2C%20an%20entrepreneur%2C%20now%20works%20as%20a%20consultant%20with%20the%20company.%20The%20conversations%20have%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20a%20partial%20owner%20of%20K%E1%BB%8D%20Caf%C3%A9%2C%20a%20name%20derived%20from%20Yoruba%20that%20means%20%26quot%3Bto%20build.%26quot%3B%20We're%20a%20West%20African%20coffee%20shop%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flong-branch-new-jersey-luxury-condos-gentrification-jersey-shore-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ENew%20Jersey%3C%2Fa%3E%20selling%20everything%20from%20basic%20coffee%2C%20tea%2C%20and%20smoothies%20to%20sandwiches%2C%20samosas%2C%20and%20Nigerian%20meat%20pies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20business%20launched%20in%202023%20with%20five%20founders%3A%20me%2C%20my%20brother%2C%20my%20cousin%2C%20and%20two%20of%20my%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20we%20leased%20the%20caf%C3%A9%20space%20as%20tenants%20for%20%241%2C400%20a%20month.%20However%2C%20we%20learned%20that%20the%203%2C600-square-foot%20building%2C%20which%20has%20two%20residential%20apartments%20above%2C%20was%20going%20to%20be%20listed%20on%20the%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20friend%20Sam%20%E2%80%94%20also%20a%20co-owner%20of%20the%20caf%C3%A9%20%E2%80%94%20and%20I%20decided%20to%20put%20an%20offer%20on%20the%20property.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESam%20and%20I%20depleted%20our%20funds%20when%20we%20renovated%20the%20caf%C3%A9%2C%20so%20we%20initially%20planned%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-raise-capital-to-buy-real-estate-property-investing-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eraise%20funds%20to%20finance%20the%20purchase%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20we%20connected%20with%20a%20Black%20venture%20capital%20group.%20A%20deal%20didn't%20work%20out%2C%20but%20one%20of%20the%20firm's%20partners%20connected%20us%20to%20a%20real%20estate%20company%20called%20Nestment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENestment%20acted%20as%20our%20co-buying%20support%20team%20during%20the%20buying%20process.%20They%20helped%20us%20find%20the%20right%20investors%20and%20connected%20us%20with%20lenders.%20The%20company%20also%20ended%20up%20co-investing%20in%20the%20building.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESam%20and%20I%20made%20an%20offer%20of%20%24740%2C000%20for%20the%20property%2C%20which%20was%20accepted.%20We%20own%2085%25%20of%20the%20building%2C%20while%20investors%2C%20including%20Nestment%2C%20own%20the%20remaining%2015%25.%20(Nestment%20also%20received%20a%20portion%20of%20the%20commission%20from%20the%20seller's%20agent.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20finance%20the%20purchase%2C%20we%20secured%20a%20debt%20service%20coverage%20ratio%20(DSCR)%20loan%20with%20a%20principal%20of%20%24555%2C000%2C%20and%20our%20monthly%20mortgage%20payment%20is%20%245%2C900.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f8f32690-3e49-4bd7-8b17-afa5dca45afb%5C%22%3EOur%20Airbnb%20income%20helps%20cover%20the%20mortgage%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe've%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-live-for-free-house-hacking-real-estate-investing-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erenting%20out%20the%20residential%20units%3C%2Fa%3E%20above%20the%20caf%C3%A9%20since%202024.%20They're%20both%20three-bedroom%2C%20two-bathroom%20apartments%2C%20each%20about%201%2C200%20square%20feet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20beginning%2C%20we%20offered%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-passive-income-hospitality-short-term-rental-airbnb-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eshort-term%20rentals%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20have%20since%20pivoted%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-investing-increasing-cash-flow-mid-term-rentals-airbnb-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emid-term%20stays%3C%2Fa%3E.%20We've%20found%20them%20to%20be%20more%20financially%20successful%20and%20better%20aligned%20with%20the%20evolving%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjersey-city-votes-increase-regulation-on-airbnb-short-term-rentals-2019-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAirbnb%20regulations%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20our%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20rentals%20typically%20last%2028%20days%20to%20a%20month%20and%20cost%20between%20%24140%20and%20%24175%20per%20day%20on%20average.%20To%20date%2C%20we%20have%20earned%20more%20than%20%24100%2C000%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-i-made-six-figures-renting-airbnb-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAirbnb%20rental%20income%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20we've%20used%20to%20supplement%20our%20mortgage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222030%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20owners%20of%20Ko%20cafe%20standing%20in%20front%20of%20the%20building.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F687e749085e81483682e5f2a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221523%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20rental%20units%20above%20the%20caf%C3%A9.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Isreal%20Adeyanju%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe've%20welcomed%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20guests%20%E2%80%94%20from%20college%20students%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdigital-nomad-life-was-hard-established-routine-notion-daily-schedule-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edigital%20nomads%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20groups%20of%20co-workers.%20However%2C%20the%20majority%20of%20our%20guests%20tend%20to%20be%20families%2C%20often%20in%20the%20area%20to%20either%20visit%20their%20children%20at%20college%20or%20help%20them%20settle%20in%20as%20they%20begin%20their%20studies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20guests%20get%20discounts%20at%20our%20caf%C3%A9%2C%20so%20the%20building%20operates%20almost%20like%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-bbs-in-america-2015-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebed%20and%20breakfast%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It's%20cool%20for%20them%20to%20be%20able%20to%20grab%20breakfast%20and%20lunch%20downstairs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2286002369-13ca-411f-bb27-821c8c8f58fb%5C%22%3EYou%20need%20trust%20to%20co-buy%20with%20a%20friend%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-bought-airbnb-made-60000-three-years-2015-07%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebuying%20a%20property%20with%20a%20friend%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20think%20the%20first%20and%20most%20important%20thing%20is%20trust.%20It%20was%20critical%20for%20us%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20in%20the%20beginning%20%E2%80%94%20because%20a%20lot%20of%20capital%20was%20being%20pooled%20into%20a%20shared%20account.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20important%20thing%20was%20understanding%20each%20other's%20individual%20goals.%20Sam%20and%20I%20both%20recognized%20that%20this%20was%20a%20key%20investment%2C%20not%20just%20for%20our%20future%20portfolios%2C%20but%20also%20to%20ensure%20the%20long-term%20security%20of%20our%20caf%C3%A9.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20also%20had%20to%20have%20a%20plan%20for%20covering%20expenses%20over%20time.%20When%20we%20bought%20the%20property%2C%20we%20opened%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fcredit-cards%2Fbest-zero-apr-business-credit-cards%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ea%20zero-interest%20credit%20card%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20I%20highly%20recommend%20to%20anyone%20buying%20a%20home.%20We%20put%20most%20of%20our%20initial%20renovation%20costs%20on%20that%20card%20and%20have%20continued%20to%20use%20it%20for%20maintenance%20expenses%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20time%20goes%20on%2C%20we%20rely%20on%20our%20reserves%20to%20cover%20ongoing%20costs%2C%20so%20we%20haven't%20had%20to%20pay%20out%20of%20pocket%20for%20any%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Isreal%20Adeyanju%20standing%20next%20to%20a%20stairwell.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F687e769485e81483682e5f77%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAdeyanju%20said%20the%20building%20is%20the%20largest%20asset%20he%20owns.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Isreal%20Adeyanju%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20a%20plan%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frental-vacation-property-manager-career-journey-lessons-advice-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erental%20management%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20important%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20beginning%2C%20we%20decided%20to%20split%20the%20responsibilities%20for%20managing%20the%20rentals.%20However%2C%20about%20six%20months%20in%2C%20I%20took%20on%20most%20of%20the%20management%2C%20as%20my%20schedule%20is%20more%20flexible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20simplify%20the%20process%2C%20we%20use%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsoftware-tools-to-grow-your-airbnb-short-term-rental-business-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ea%20lot%20of%20apps%20and%20AI%20tools%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20though%20we%20also%20use%